		<pubDate>Thu, 14 Aug 2014 02:03:50 +0000</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://jamesclear-com.uar9g7bv-liquidwebsites.com/?p=6042#comment-10844</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[There are a number of randomized and controlled trials researching the effects of music with clinical populations that have clearly defined as active vs passive or listening vs live. Furthermore, there are a number of meta-analyses of the existing research that use accepted forms of statistical analysis to examine the effects of music - these are able to look at larger numbers due to combining studies. &quot;Large&quot; numbers in trials are problematic due to the nature of the populations i.e. medical studies also struggle to get &quot;large&quot; numbers in complex populations, and it is typically complex populations with music therapy is used as a clinical intervention. Do examine the best evidence about music therapy and music medicine research, you need to look at the Cochrane Library. http://www.thecochranelibrary.com/view/0/index.html]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>There are a number of randomized and controlled trials researching the effects of music with clinical populations that have clearly defined as active vs passive or listening vs live. Furthermore, there are a number of meta-analyses of the existing research that use accepted forms of statistical analysis to examine the effects of music &#8211; these are able to look at larger numbers due to combining studies. &#8220;Large&#8221; numbers in trials are problematic due to the nature of the populations i.e. medical studies also struggle to get &#8220;large&#8221; numbers in complex populations, and it is typically complex populations with music therapy is used as a clinical intervention. Do examine the best evidence about music therapy and music medicine research, you need to look at the Cochrane Library. <a href="http://www.thecochranelibrary.com/view/0/index.html" rel="nofollow ugc">http://www.thecochranelibrary.com/view/0/index.html</a></p>
]]></content:encoded>
		
